      <h1 class='title'>British Council: Indemnities</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 25 November 2004 vol 667 cc11-2WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_11ws' title='Col. 11WS &mdash; HL Deb 25 November 2004 vol 667 c11WS' name='column_11ws' href='#column_11ws' rel='bookmark'>11WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0667P0-08710'>
        <a name='S5LV0667P0_20041125_LWS_7'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-elizabeth-symons' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041125_LWS_7' title='Link to this speech by Ms Elizabeth Symons' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-elizabeth-symons" title="Ms Elizabeth Symons">The Minister of State, Foreign and Commonwealth Office (Baroness Symons of Vernham Dean)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0667P0-08710">The British Council, although not a government department, receives a substantial grant-in-aid from the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. The council regularly organises or sponsors exhibitions overseas of works of art loaned from national galleries and private collections in the United Kingdom. It provides certain assurances or guarantees in respect of loss or damage while these works are on loan.</p><p id="S5LV0667P0-08711">In the six months ending on 30 September 2004, the British Council provided such assurances to four national lenders and undertakings to 85 private
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_12ws' title='Col. 12WS &mdash; HL Deb 25 November 2004 vol 667 c12WS' name='column_12ws' href='#column_12ws' rel='bookmark'>12WS</a>
          lenders. The value of the contingent liabilities outstanding on 30 September in respect of private lenders was &#x00A3;6,120,870. No liabilities to national galleries existed at that date.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
